Fig. 2. Classification of legislative electoral systems.

library(tidyverse)

es_raw <- read_rds("source__es-data-v3.rds")

es <-
  es_raw %>%
  filter(presidential == 0, ! is.na(classification)) %>%
  mutate(
    classification = if_else(str_detect(classification, "Divisor|Quota"), "List", classification),
    electoral_rule = paste(type_short, classification, sep = "-")
    )

rule <-
  es %>%
  group_by(country, electoral_rule) %>%
  summarise(across(c("tier1_avemag", "upperseats", "enep", "enpp"), mean, na.rm = TRUE)) %>%
  group_by(electoral_rule) %>%
  summarise(n_ctry = n(),
            across(where(is.numeric), ~ mean(.x, na.rm = TRUE) %>% round(1))) %>%
  mutate(enp_diff = enep - enpp)

Quiz

rule_quiz <- rule %>% filter(electoral_rule != "Pro-STV")

Which of the capital letters A to E is a summary of which electoral system?

  • Maj-Absolute-Majority, Maj-Plurality, Mix-Dependent, Mix-Independent, Pro-List
  • Pro-STV removed from quiz to avoid confusion

Parameters

  • tier1_avemag â€“ average district magnitude lowest tier
  • upperseats â€“ number of seats in districts above lowest tier
  • enep â€“ effective number electoral parties
  • enpp â€“ effective number parliamentary parties
set.seed(1234)
rule_quiz %>%
  slice(sample(1:n())) %>%
  mutate(electoral_rule = LETTERS[1:n()]) %>%
  select(-n_ctry, -enp_diff)
